cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.VR, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the challenge of alphanumeric text entry in VR and compares different hand representations for typing. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper discusses the visualization of hands and fingers in VR. 
- cs.VR (Virtual Reality) is another possible category as the paper specifically addresses the challenge of typing in VR. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves the retrieval of text input from users in VR. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the use of video inlay for hand representation in VR.
